WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.323
Etiologically, viral pathogens — particularly enteroviruses

00:00:03.323 --> 00:00:06.646
and adenoviruses — remain the most

00:00:06.646 --> 00:00:07.754
common cause.

00:00:07.754 --> 00:00:11.077
Autoimmune conditions including lupus, sarcoidosis, and

00:00:11.077 --> 00:00:14.400
giant cell disease account for a

00:00:14.400 --> 00:00:15.508
significant subset.

00:00:15.508 --> 00:00:18.831
Emerging causes include immune checkpoint inhibitors,

00:00:18.831 --> 00:00:22.154
occurring in approximately one percent of

00:00:22.154 --> 00:00:25.477
treated oncology patients, and mRNA COVID-19

00:00:25.477 --> 00:00:28.800
vaccine-associated myocarditis, predominantly in young males.
